description:
&lt;p&gt;A new role has been created to support the delivery of practice placement growth within the South West region. This exciting role will allow the successful candidate the opportunity to work with provider organisations across the region to maximise opportunities to expand clinical placement opportunities for healthcare students and learners working across systems and pathways .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also have responsibility for establishing solutions with providers within ICS footprints to design systems and solutions to enable the ongoing monitoring of placement capacity and utilisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will have experience of managing clinical placements within an educational context and will be able to demonstrate a sound understanding of the challenges and issues of providing clinical practice placement experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the role will require significant networking and collaboration with provider organisations and HEIs, good communication skills and the ability to lead meetings confidently will be key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 8a with a full-time starting salary of £45,753, with a pay step increase after 5 years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teresa Hewitt-Moran, Director of Performance &amp; Delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: teresa.hewitt-moran@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
